• Place the heel of one hand in the centre of the victim's chest (which is the lower half of the victim's breastbone).\n
• Place the heel of your other hand on top of the first hand.\n
• Interlock the fingers of your hands and ensure that pressure is not applied over the victim's ribs. Keep your arms straight.\n
• Do not apply any pressure over the upper abdomen or the bottom end of the sternum (breastbone).\n
• Position yourself vertically above the victim's chest and press down on the sternum at least 5cm (but not exceeding 6cm).\n
• After each compression, release all the pressure on the chest without losing contact between your hands and the sternum; repeat at a rate of at least 100 per minute (but not exceeding 120 per minute).\n
• Compression and release should take equal amounts of time."
