• If the victim is wearing spectacles, remove them.\n
• Place the arm nearest to you out at right angles to the body, elbow bent with the hand palm uppermost (Figure 2.17).\n
• Bring the far arm across the chest, and hold the back of the hand against the victim's cheek nearest to you (Figure 2.18).\n
• With your other hand, grasp the far leg just above the knee and pull it up, keeping the foot on the ground.\n
• Keeping the hand pressed against the cheek, pull on the far leg to roll the victim towards you onto his side.\n
• Adjust the upper leg so that both hip and knee are bent at right angles.\n
• Tilt the head back to make sure the airway remains open.\n
• Adjust the victim's hand under the cheek, if necessary, to keep the head tilted (Figure 2.20).\n
• Check breathing regularly."
